Malignant melanoma treatment can be segmented by treatment type, distribution channel, and region. In terms of treatment type, the market is divided into immunotherapy, targeted therapy, chemotherapy, surgery, radiation therapy, and others. Immunotherapy and targeted therapy have gained increasing prominence in the treatment of malignant melanoma due to their efficacy and targeted approach. The distribution channels for these treatments include hospitals, clinics, cancer research institutes, retail pharmacies, online pharmacies, and others. Geographically, the market is categorized into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East and Africa, with North America leading in terms of market share due to technological advancements, increasing prevalence of melanoma, and well-established healthcare infrastructure.

